INTRODUCTION
------------

Cmp-daemon is a little C program for Macbooks, which dynamically controls the 
fan speed of Core Duo CPUs to keep the MacBook cold.
It was developed and tested on Archlinux with the following basic configuration:

Model: MacbookPro3,1
CPU:   Core Duo 2200 MHz


Start the daemon:
bash-3.2# /etc/rc.d/cmp-daemon start
:: Starting cmp-daemond 

Stop the daemon:
bash-3.2# /etc/rc.d/cmp-daemon stop
:: Stopping cmp-daemond 

Check status:
bash-3.2# more /var/log/daemon.log | grep cmp-daemon
Dec 12 21:22:36 intel2200 macbook[3186]: CPU: model name	: Intel(R) Core(TM)2 Duo CPU     T7500  @ 2.20GHz
Dec 12 21:22:36 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Start
Dec 12 21:22:37 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 1: fan speed 2000 RPM temperature 32 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:52:05 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 2: fan speed 2240 RPM temperature 52 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:52:08 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 3: fan speed 2000 RPM temperature 46 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:53:44 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 4: fan speed 2400 RPM temperature 53 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:54:17 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 5: fan speed 2000 RPM temperature 46 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:54:53 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 6: fan speed 2720 RPM temperature 55 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:55:05 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 7: fan speed 2000 RPM temperature 50 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:55:38 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 8: fan speed 2400 RPM temperature 53 degree celsius
Dec 12 22:55:55 intel2200 macbook[3187]: Change 9: fan speed 2000 RPM temperature 47 degree celsius


MANUAL INSTALLATION
------------
load the applesmc modul:
bash-3.2# modprobe applesmc -v

compile the C program: 
gcc -Wall cmp-daemon.c

copy the  C program to:
cp cmp-daemon /usr/sbin/

and the start script to:
cp cmp-daemon /etc/rc.d/

If you want the daemon to be started at system boot, add the daemon and applesmc module int your rc.conf:

nano /etc/rc.conf
MODULES=(applesmc)
DAEMONS=(cmp-daemon)

